      • addDefaultPrefixModule

        public SamuraiClientBuilder addDefaultPrefixModule(java.lang.String prefix)
        Define the default prefix of new guilds. If this is not set, a DefaultPrefixModule with prefix ! is added.

        This module comes with a PrefixCommand that allows members to check the prefix of the guild and allows administrators to change the prefix.

        Make Sure to include an AdminModule through addAdminModule(java.util.function.Predicate<net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.Member>) or addAdminModule(Predicate) otherwise the guild prefix can be changed by any member.

        This method's implementation is: 

         addModule(new DefaultPrefixModule(prefix))

        You can define a different prefix implementation by providing a class to addModule(IModule...) that implements IPrefixModule

      • addDefaultAdminModule

        public SamuraiClientBuilder addDefaultAdminModule()
        This enables the @Admin annotation that is marked on Command classes. This ensures that Commands marked with @Admin are only usable by Administrators.

        It is important to include an implementation of IAdminModule through either this method, addAdminModule(Predicate), or your own implementation. Otherwise, all users will have access to Administrative Commands

        The default criteria for defining an Administrator is as follows:

        • Has Kick Members Permission
        • Is higher than the bot on the role hierarchy

        Different criteria to determine which member has administrative status with addAdminModule(Predicate) or your own implementation of IAdminModule

      • addAdminModule

        public SamuraiClientBuilder addAdminModule(java.util.function.Predicate<net.dv8tion.jda.core.entities.Member> isAdmin)
        Define custom behavior to determine which members can use Commands marked with @Admin

        This method's implementation is: 

         addModule(new DefaultAdminModule(isAdmin))
